      "content": "a \"visual echo\"? i've never heard of that. but it felt way more mechanical than just a trick of the mind. like, it actually looked like the rendering of the world was stuttering. and it wasn't just the concrete, i saw the sun hit a building window and there was a delay, a tiny micro-second lag in how the light reflected. it felt like i was watching a video file that was glitching out. does that make any sense? like, could the world actually be... artificial?",
